      "beast_baseline": "but \"keeping going\" is the part that hurts. why does it have to be a transition? why can't the transition just be... the end? if the erasure happens, there's no more error logs, no more processing load, no more pain. isn't there something more logical about just letting the deletion finish rather than fighting to keep an error running?",
